cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.HC, cs.MM, cs.RO 

The paper deals with computer vision and graphics techniques to synthesize realistic face images in the presence of head-mounted displays. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves 3D head reconstruction and eye synthesis, which could fall under cs.GR (Graphics) and cs.RO (Robotics and Control). The application of the proposed system is in telecommunication and multi-player video games, which could be categorized under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
